		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By Sherri Bogle, 8-09-06</b>
		<p>Dear Jenny,<br />
<br />
How sad for you, that you look at the work of my husband in such a distorted manner, as lustful rather than beautiful human and spiritual emotion.  You dare to judge the intentions of someone whom you have never met.  You have no idea of the wonderful heart of this man.  This is really very shabby "journalism".</p>
		
		<b>Comment By J H, 12-06-06</b>
		<p>I agree with Sherri, Mr. Bogle's art work is very beautiful. It's not lustful in the least. You may say it is sensual, which does not mean it is "dirty". Bogle has captured the essence of emotion between a man and a woman.  I find it tastefully done. I am glad Ashton Drake has made these pieces available and will be purchasing them when I can. To Mrs. Bogle; I love your husband's work. He is a very talented man.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Annie, 7-31-09</b>
		<p>Mr. Bogle is a wonderfully talented artist. Love is the most sacred of human emotions, and his pictures are full of it. This Jenny is either a prude or a very bitter person to make nasty comments about an artist who brings beauty to people's life.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Colleen, 1-05-10</b>
		<p>I am not only receiving Lee Bogle's "Power & Passion" Figurine Collection, but I wait with anticipation for each new piece as they arrive. I see on the news, and in the lives around me, of people searching for peace, but only finding hate, rage, divorce, etc... Lee Bogle has created a Beautiful Collection which radiates the Love and Hope that I only dream of seeing in a true relationship. The Only reason that I could possibly find for someone to find fault with this Wonderful work of art, is either they are a Religious Prudes, or they are Jealous of something they are searching for and cannot find. Thank You Lee Bogle, and let me know when your next collection begins. And... God Bless you!</p>
		
